{{Infobox language |name=Ebrié |nativename=Cama |pronunciation={{IPA|[tʃamã]}} |states=[[Ivory Coast]] |region=[[Abidjan Department|Abidjan]] |speakers=76,000 |date=1988 census |ref = e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Kwa languages|Kwa]] |fam4=[[Potou–Tano languages|Potou–Tano]] |fam5=[[Potou languages|Potou]] |iso3=ebr |glotto=ebri1238 |glottorefname=Ebrie }}
'''Ebrié''', or '''Cama''' (Caman, Kyama, Tchaman, Tsama, Tyama), is spoken in [[Ivory Coast]] and [[Ghana]]. It is a [[Potou language]] of the [[Kwa languages|Kwa]] branch of the [[Niger–Congo]] family of languages.
