{{Infobox website |name = {{Wiki favicon}} Swedish Wikipedia |logo = Wikipedia-logo-v2-sv.png |logo_size = 135px |logocaption = |screenshot = SwedishWikipediaMainpageScreenshot9thSeptember2012.png |screenshot_size = 280px |collapsible = yes |caption = The Main Page of the Swedish Wikipedia on 9 September 2012. |url = {{URL|sv.wikipedia.org/}} |slogan = |commercial = No |type = [[Internet encyclopedia project]] |registration = Optional |language = [[Swedish language|Swedish]] |content license = |owner = [[Wikimedia Foundation]] |author = |launch date = {{Start date and age|2001|5|23}} }} The '''Swedish Wikipedia''' ({{lang-{{#property:P424}}|{{#property:P1448}}}}) is the [[Swedish language|Swedish-language]] edition of [[Wikipedia]] and was started on 23 May 2001.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sv.wikipedia.com/wiki.cgi?action=history&id=HomePage |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010608192645/sv.wikipedia.com/wiki.cgi?action=history&id=HomePage |title=Wikipedia: History of HomePage |archivedate=8 June 2001 |accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref> It is currently the third largest Wikipedia by article-count with its {{formatnum:{{NUMBEROF|ARTICLES|sv}}}} current articles,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/List_of_Wikipedias |title=List of Wikipedias - Meta |website=meta.wikimedia.org |access-date=18 October 2017}}</ref> where a majority are generated by a [[Internet bot|bot]], or software application,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/senastenytt/ttnyheter/inrikes/article22752344.ab |title=Kontroversiell robot bakom wikiväxt |work=Aftonbladet |language= sv |access-date=2017-10-18}}</ref> and has a [[:meta:Wikipedia article depth|''Wikipedia article depth'']] of 5.6. The [[Wikipedia administrators|administrators]] on the Swedish Wikipedia (currently {{NUMBEROF|ADMINS|sv|N}}) are elected for a [[term of office|fixed-term period]] of one year and have to be re-elected after that time.<ref>{{Cite web |date= 18 October 2017 |title= Wikipedia:Administratörer |url=https://sv.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Administrat%C3%B6rer&oldid=41219804 |website=Wikipedia |language=sv}}</ref>
== History ==
[[File:Sv-wp-svenska-2001.png|thumb|upright=1.3|Screenshot on 23 May 2001 of sv.wikipedia.com]] Originally, Swedish Wikipedia rivalled [[susning.nu]], a [[wiki]] created by [[Lars Aronsson]] in 2001. Susning.nu was by 28 May 2003 the world's second largest wiki. Due to several controversies involving the authority of the founder, objections to Aronsson's decision to allow [[advertisement]] on the site, several prolific Susning writers switched over to Swedish Wikipedia in 2002, and later more followed. Two of its pioneers were Johan Dahlin and Dan Köhl, the latter one introduced "''Tinget''" in November 2002. This was the first conflict handling organ at Swedish Wikipedia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sv.wikisource.org/wiki/S%C3%A5_fungerar_Wikipedia/Wikipedias_historia#Tinget_och_skilkom |title=Så fungerar Wikipedia/Wikipedias historia |publisher=Lennart Guldbrandsson, sv.wikisource.org |date=2010-03-09 |accessdate=2015-11-24}}</ref> In April 2004, Susning.nu's editing features were closed down to all but a handful of users, which further increased the flow to Swedish Wikipedia. On 14 January 2005, Wikipedia's article count surpassed that of Susning.nu.{{Citation needed|date=March 2008}}
In March 2006, the Swedish newspaper ''[[Svenska Dagbladet]]'' published a comparative evaluation of Swedish Wikipedia, Susning.nu and the online version of [[Nationalencyklopedin]]. The evaluation was done by giving a selection of articles to independent subject matter experts for grading. While Nationalencyklopedin came out on top with respect to factuality and neutrality, Swedish Wikipedia received a good overall grade and came out on top with respect to being up to date and having a broad coverage, also including popular culture subjects.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gratis nätlexikon får bra betyg |first=Ulrika |last=Nandra |url=http://www.svd.se/kultur/gratis-natlexikon-far-bra-betyg_305804.svd |newspaper=[[Svenska Dagbladet]] |language=Swedish |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zc78dWm1 |archivedate=21 June 2011 |date=30 March 2006 |accessdate=21 June 2011}}</ref>
On 27 September 2012 it reached 500,000 articles.<ref>{{cite press release |title=Grattis Sverige - nu har vi en halv miljon Wikipedia-artiklar! |publisher=Wikimedia Sverige |date=27 September 2012 |url=http://nyheter.se.msn.com/photopage.aspx?cp-documentid=251471807 |language=Swedish |accessdate=27 September 2012}}</ref> On 15 June 2013 it reached 1,000,000 articles and rose from 8th to 5th place.<ref>[http://meta.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_Wikipedias&oldid=5527567 "List of Wikipedias".] Meta.wikimedia.org, 2013-06-16. Retrieved 16 June 2013.</ref> This meant that during 2012 and 2013 the number of articles on Swedish Wikipedia more than doubled. This is in large part due to a community project where [[Internet bot|bot]]s were used in producing articles for all existing species of plants and animals. When finished, this project alone created more than a million articles, most short and sourced through available online databases on the subject.<ref>[http://sv.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Användare:Lsjbot&oldid=18990516 "Användare:Lsjbot".] Sv.wikipedia.org. Retrieved 16 June 2013. {{sv}} Machine translation: [https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=sv&sl=sv&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fsv.wikipedia.org%2Fw%2Findex.php%3Ftitle%3DAnvändare%3ALsjbot%26oldid%3D18990516]</ref> In 2014 about half of its articles were created by [[Lsjbot|a single bot]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.wikimedia.org/2013/06/17/swedish-wikipedia-1-million-articles/ |title=Swedish Wikipedia surpasses 1 million articles with aid of article creation bot « Wikimedia blog |publisher=Blog.wikimedia.org |date= |accessdate=2014-08-03}}</ref>
